# Synthesis Phase: Ensemble & Final Validation

Objective: Combine the three validated boosters using Rank-Based Blending and Multi-Seed Averaging to achieve maximum ROC AUC stability.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> Rank Blending is chosen over Stacking because the boosters have highly similar performance on OOF/LB, making them ideal for rank-based consensus.

## Proposed Changes

### [Ensemble & Blending]

#### [NEW] [synthesis_blender.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/new-challenge/synthesis_blender.py)
- Load OOF predictions for CatBoost, XGBoost, and LightGBM.
- Calculate Spearman Rank Correlation to verify diversity.
- Implement Weighted Rank-Based Averaging.
- Generate `submission_synthesis_v1.csv`.

#### [NEW] [multi_seed_refiner.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/new-challenge/multi_seed_refiner.py)
- Refine the best performing booster (XGB or Cat) with 3 different seeds.
- Average seeds to reduce variance before final blend.

### [Guardrails & Submission]

#### [NEW] [judge_guard.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/new-challenge/judge_guard.py)
- Implement 7-Gate Submit Protocol:
  1. Intent, 2. Identity, 3. Format, 4. Sanity, 5. Dtype, 6. Value, 7. Risk Gates.
- Final validation against [trinity_config.json](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/new-challenge/trinity_config.json) thresholds.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `python3 synthesis_blender.py --audit` (Correlation check).
- `python3 judge_guard.py submission_synthesis_v1.csv` (7-Gate check).

### Manual Verification
- Review Rank Correlation matrix in logs.
- Final LB submission and OOF vs LB gap check.
